<br>
Do the airlines change all their seats to business class because 5% of their customers will pay it? Do credit card companies get rid of their normal services because 10% of their customers will go for platinum service? Hell no.<br>
<br>
Verant is making their own version of premium service. Almost every kind of service industry has this sort of thing, be it a membership card for discounts or what have you. Valet parking, etc... It's all the same thing.<br>
<br>
Verant would lose TONS of they switched all the servers to the Legends format. They couldn't support the manpower it would take, and they'd lose massive amounts of customer base. It would be financial suicide. They know this already. They've run the tests and polls themselves. I'm sure we all answered that little quiz when it popped up on log-in. Do you remember it? They are running with what some of their customers are willing to pay to have.<br>
<br>
I say good for them. Those who want it can have it. The rest of us can enjoy the trickle-down improvements at a later date, without losing what we have now.<br>
<br>
Doomsayers are always the first and loudest to speak. Wait a month or two after Legends releases, and come back and think of all these predictions. See what's come true, and what was just knee-jerk reaction.<br>
